name: Kenna Security
description: This app integrates with Kenna Security to implement various investigative actions

actions.description: Validate the asset configuration for connectivity using supplied configuration
List patches for a specified device
actions.verbose:
If parameter Vulnerability ID is provided then other parameters would be ignored.
If user requires data based on IP, Hostname or MAC Address then he needs to select appropriate filter type and provide related value for it.

vulnerability_id.description: ID of the vulnerability for patches

example_values: Updated Grid component packages that fix several security issues, add various enhancements and fix multiple bugs are now available for Red Hat Enterprise MRG 2 for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.The Red Hat Security Response Team has rated this update as having moderate security impact.

• condor on Red Hat Enterprise Linux

    Upgrade condor

    Update condor to the latest version available from Red Hat, using tools like yum or up2date.

  • condor-aviary on Red Hat Enterprise Linux

    Upgrade condor-aviary

    Update condor-aviary to the latest version available from Red Hat, using tools like yum or up2date.
RHSA-2012:1281: Red Hat Enterprise MRG Grid 2.2 security update

actions.verbose:
At least one of ID or IP or Hostname needs to be provided as a parameter.
Priority would be given in order of ID, IP and Hostname.

active.description: Status of the device (Default: No action)

actions.verbose:
The parameter search must contain any valid parameter found in data of assets for filtering.
The search string entered by user should be in format "Parameter:Value".
Some examples of valid search string are as follows:
  • primary_locator:mac_address
  • hostname:foobar
  • max_priority:10&min_priority:1
  • service_ports:8080

connector.description: ID or name of the connector

actions.verbose:
The due date should be entered in YYYY-MM-DD or valid "iso8601 timestamp" format.
Some examples of valid time formats are:
  • 2018-09-24
  • 2018-09-23T14:40:44Z
  • 2018-09-23T14:40:44+05:30
  • 2020-08-30T01:45:36.123Z
  • 2021-12-13T21:20:37.593194+05:30

priority.description: Priority flag for vulnerability (Default: No action)

due_date.description: Due date for vulnerability (YYYY-MM-DD or valid iso8601 format)

actions.description: Get vulnerabilities for a specific device

example_values: Unspecified vulnerability in the Deployment component in Java Runtime Environment (JRE) in Oracle Java SE and Java for Business 6 Update 23 and earlier allows remote untrusted Java Web Start applications and untrusted Java applets to affect confidentiality, integrity, and availability via unknown vectors.

actions.verbose:
If parameter search is provided then all other parameters are ignored.
The search string must contain any valid parameter found in data of vulnerabilities for filtering.
The search string entered by user should be in format "Parameter:Value".
Some examples of valid search string are as follows:
  • cve:2014-0160
  • hostname:foobar
  • max_priority:10&min_priority:1
  • top_priority:true

example_values: Unspecified vulnerability in the Java Runtime Environment (JRE) component in Oracle Java SE 7 Update 2 and earlier, 6 Update 30 and earlier, and JavaFX 2.0.2 and earlier allows remote untrusted Java Web Start applications and untrusted Java applets to affect confidentiality, integrity, and availability via unknown vectors related to Deployment.
